    <note type="biography">
        <p>Scottish anatomist. Croonian Lecturer, Royal Society of London, 1860. House surgeon, Edinburgh Royal Infirmary, 1861. Assistant, Hunterian Museum, Royal College of Surgeons of England, 1862–7. Curator, museum of the Royal College of Surgeons of Edinburgh, 1869; lecturer in physiology, 1873. Chandos Professor of medicine and anatomy and dean of the medical faculty, St Andrews University, 1875. Represented the universities of Glasgow and St Andrews on the General Medical Council, 1877–86. FRS 1869.</p></note>
